Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: 0
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: Weight training and DHEA supplement will help raise testosterone naturally.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Clinical Recommendations: No abnormalities detected
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Monitor hearing annually

Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.

------------------------------
Employee: Jashwin Maharaj
Report Date: 2020-10-06
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Supplement with vitamin D3 - 35000iu weekly or 5000iu daily. Recheck levels in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/ml.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations:

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level
Mild component of hearing loss at 250 hz
Slightly low DHEA

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Nil
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Generally in good health on the day of examination.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations:

Overview Notes: Strong history of heart disease on Maternal side of family
Comment Key: ClinicalExamNote
Comment Value: Mild hearing loss at 250hz
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Non smoker
Minimal alcohol consumption
Regular exercise

Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: Please review any new urinary difficulties with your doctor.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Supplement with vitamin D3 - 35000iu weekly or 5000iu daily. Recheck levels in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/ml.

Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.
Comment Key: EyesightRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: Please review any new urinary difficulties with your doctor.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Supplement with vitamin D3 - 35000iu weekly or 5000iu daily. Recheck levels in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/ml.
Comment Key: LabTestNote
Comment Value: Suboptimal vitamin D level
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.

Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.
Comment Key: LifestyleNote
Comment Value: None

------------------------------
Employee: Jashwin Maharaj
Report Date: 2020-10-06
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: 0
Comment Key: LifestyleRecommendation
Comment Value: None

Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.
Comment Key: MedicalHistoryNote
Comment Value: None

Clinical Recommendations: No abnormalities detected
Men's Health Recommendations: Weight training and DHEA supplement will help raise testosterone naturally.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Supplement with vitamin D3 - 35000iu weekly or 5000iu daily. Recheck levels in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/ml.
Comment Key: MedicalHistoryNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.
Comment Key: MedicalHistoryRecommendation
Comment Value: Family history cardiac disease is associated with a risk of early cardiac disease, it's important you keep up with your annual checks
Special Investigation Notes: Nil
------------------------------
Employee: Jashwin Maharaj

Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: 0

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Strong history of heart disease on Maternal side of family
Comment Key: MedicalHistoryRecommendation
Comment Value: Family history cardiac disease is associated with a risk of early cardiac disease, it's important you keep up with your annual checks
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Supplement with vitamin D3 - 35000iu weekly or 5000iu daily. Recheck levels in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/ml.
Comment Key: MensHealthNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Monitor hearing annually
Comment Key: MensHealthRecommendation

Women's Health Recommendations:

Overview Notes: Supplement with vitamin D3 - 35000iu weekly or 5000iu daily. Recheck levels in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/ml.
Comment Key: MentalHealthAnxietyRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Overview Notes: Supplement with vitamin D3 - 35000iu weekly or 5000iu daily. Recheck levels in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/ml.
Comment Key: MentalHealthAnxietyRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil
------------------------------
Employee: Jashwin Maharaj
Report Date: 2020-10-06
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: No abnormalities detected
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.

Men's Health Recommendations: Please review any new urinary difficulties with your doctor.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.
Comment Key: MentalHealthMoodRecommendation

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Nil
Comment Key: MentalHealthNote

Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: 0
Comment Key: MentalHealthNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Employee: Jashwin Maharaj
Report Date: 2020-10-06
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Supplement with vitamin D3 - 35000iu weekly or 5000iu daily. Recheck levels in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/ml.

Report Date: 2020-10-06
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: No abnormalities detected
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Supplement with vitamin D3 - 35000iu weekly or 5000iu daily. Recheck levels in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/ml.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level
Mild component of hearing loss at 250 hz
Slightly low DHEA

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Monitor hearing annually

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level
Mild component of hearing loss at 250 hz
Slightly low DHEA

Overview Notes: Supplement with vitamin D3 - 35000iu weekly or 5000iu daily. Recheck levels in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/ml.
Comment Key: SymptomScreeningNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Special Investigation Notes: Nil
------------------------------
Employee: Jashwin Maharaj
Report Date: 2020-10-06
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.
Comment Key: SymptomScreeningNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Non smoker
Minimal alcohol consumption
Regular exercise
Comment Key: SymptomScreeningRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level
Mild component of hearing loss at 250 hz
Slightly low DHEA

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Generally in good health on the day of examination.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Low Dhea may reflect that your body has been under stress, which is most likely due to having been affected by COVID-19 and losing your mother-in-law. Make self care and stress reduction a priority.
Comment Key: VitaminsOrSupplements
Comment Value: Multivitamin , omega
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level
Mild component of hearing loss at 250 hz
Slightly low DHEA
Comment Key: WomensHealthNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil
------------------------------
Employee: Jashwin Maharaj
Report Date: 2020-10-06
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Generally in good health on the day of examination.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Supplement with vitamin D3 - 35000iu weekly or 5000iu daily. Recheck levels in 4 to 6 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/ml.

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
